Herndon Capital Management, LLC Hires Vice President of Client Service, and Senior Equity Trader

Posted on February 9, 2012 by StreetID 

Atlanta, GA – FEB 2012 Herndon Capital Management, LLC (“HCM”) today announced the additions of Antoinette Bing Scroggins, Vice President of Client Services and Kenneth Jackson, Senior Equity Trader.

Ms. Scroggins brings over 10 years industry experience in institutional trading and operations, business development and client servicing. She has a proven track record of successfully building solid, long-term relationships with institutional investors. In her role, Ms. Scroggins will be responsible for broadening and solidifying HCM’s relationships with its clients.
Mr. Jackson brings his many years of equity trading experience to HCM. He has traded in both domestic and international markets. Kenny will be responsible for trading all the equity products offered by HCM.
“The unique skill set Antoinette acquired during her tenure on the sell side will prove to be very beneficial to HCM as we remain dedicated to meeting our clients’ needs during this tremendous growth phase of our business,” said Arlene Pine, HCM’s Director of Marketing & Client Services.
Annette Marshall, HCM’s Chief Compliance Officer said, “We are very excited about the addition of Kenny Jackson to our Trading team. He brings extensive experience in trading both domestic and international securities, which will complement our existing trading platform and will position us for continued growth in all products.”
Antoinette B. Scroggins
Vice President, Client Services
Antoinette brings 10 years of experience in the financial services industry to HCM. Prior to joining the firm, Antoinette managed the institutional sales and trading desk at BOE Securities. She served as the head trader and was responsible for managing existing client relationships, identifying new business opportunities and back office functions. Prior to joining BOE Securities, Inc., she worked on the institutional sales and trading desk at The Malachi Group, a boutique Investment Banking firm, where she was responsible for institutional sales and trading, operations and compliance.
Antoinette completed her BBA in Finance from Saint Joseph’s University. She successfully passed the FINRA licensing exams: Series 7, 24, 55, and 63.
Kenneth R. Jackson
Senior Equity Trader
Kenny brings 16 years of experience in the investment management industry. Prior to joining HCM, he was a Principal at Qubit Investments, LLC where he helped manage a start-up Equity Market Neutral Hedge Fund, which included responsibility for daily trading operations.  Prior to joining Qubit Investments, Kenny spent 14 years at Delaware Investments. Kenny served as an Equity Quantitative Analyst for seven years providing risk management and modeling for Large Cap Value, Small Cap Value and Core products. He also served as a member of the Large Cap Value Portfolio Construction Committee. In 2008, Kenny joined the Equity Trading Desk executing both domestic and international securities. During his tenure as part of the international trading team, they ranked #1 globally vs. VWAP via the Elkins McSherry global transaction cost analysis 2009 survey.
Kenneth graduated from Hampton University with a Bachelor of Science degree in finance in 1996.
About Herndon Capital Management, LLC (HCM):
Founded and registered with the SEC in 2001, HCM is an institutional money management firm specializing in U.S. and international large- and mid-cap equity strategies. At the end of DEC 2011 HCM had approximately 175 client relationships and close to $5 billion of assets under management.
For more information, please visit us at www.herndoncapital.com or contact Arlene Pine, CFA, Director of Marketing and Client Services via phone at (404) 232-8832 or via email at apine@herndoncap.com.
 

